            <p class="teaser"><a href="https://www.npr.org/2023/11/07/1197956576/rap-sh-t-is-still-musing-on-music-and-art-of-making-it"><time datetime="2023-11-07"><span class="date">November 7, 2023 &#149; </span></time>The Max series <em>Rap Sh!t</em> feels like a comedy for The Moment. Created by Issa Rae, the show focuses on Shawna and Mia (played by Aida Osman and KaMillion), two aspiring rappers from Miami, and documents the challenges they face as young women trying to break into the music industry. The show is about to return for a second season, so today we're revisiting our conversation about the series.</a></p>

            

